(
<figureCitation id="8BE183E1FF964E07FC8FBCE12390FA63" box="[836,910,1465,1487]" captionStart="Figg" captionStartId="11.[151,196,1882,1904]" captionTargetBox="[157,1394,233,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-44@11.[151,1398,231,1872]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figg. 1-12: Habitus. 1. Ischnopoda pulchritudinis n. sp.; 2. Xyronarchusa amazonica n. gen., n. sp.; 3. Atheta (Acrotona) obscurepyga n. sp.; 4. Atheta (Acrotona) tanpokensis n. sp.; 5. Atheta (Acrotona) guyterminicornis n. sp.; 6. Atheta (Acrotona) subparcior n. sp.; 7. Atheta (Acrotona) guyminima n. sp.; 8. Atheta (Microdota) ungulifera n. sp.; 9. Atheta (Microdota) guyarufa n. sp.; 10. Atheta (Xestota) guyattenuata n. sp.; 11. Atheta (Datomicra) guymimetica n. sp.; 12. Atheta (Datomicra) guydivergens n. sp." pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Figg. 2 e</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="8BE183E1FF964E07FC58BCE123DAFA63" box="[915,964,1465,1487]" captionStart="Figg" captionStartId="13.[151,196,1884,1906]" captionTargetBox="[160,1388,235,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-44@13.[151,1398,232,1873]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figg. 24-37: Edeago in visione laterale e ventrale, spermateca, labio con palpo labiale, maxilla con palpo maxillare e mento. 24-25. Ischnopoda pulchritudinis n. sp.; 26-29. Xyronarchusa amazonica n. gen., n. sp.; 30-32. Atheta (Acrotona) obscurepyga n. sp.; 33-35. Atheta (Acrotona) tanpokensis n. sp.; 36-37. Atheta (Acrotona) guyterminicornis n. sp." pageId="1" pageNumber="94">26-29</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="13659F64FF964E04FCD1BCB12291FECD" blockId="1.[794,1399,1513,2082]" lastBlockId="2.[189,794,233,353]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="95" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FCD1BCB12361F9AD" bold="true" box="[794,895,1513,1537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Diagnosi</emphasis>
: Habitus simile ad 
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF964E07FB99BCB12551F9AD" authority="THOMSON, 1858" authorityName="THOMSON" authorityYear="1858" box="[1106,1359,1513,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FB99BCB12487F9AD" box="[1106,1177,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Atheta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="774BE295FF964E07FB6BBCB12551F9AD" author="THOMSON, C. G." box="[1184,1359,1513,1537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" pagination="27 - 40" refId="ref9217" refString="THOMSON, C. G. 1858: Forsok till uppstallning af Sveriges Staphyliner. - Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps- Akademiens Forhandlinger 15: 27 - 40." type="journal article" year="1858">THOMSON, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
del sottogenere 
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FC54BF51241FF98C" box="[927,1025,1545,1568]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Acrotona</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="774BE295FF964E07FBC2BF5124A5F98D" author="THOMSON, C. G." box="[1033,1211,1545,1569]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" pagination="27 - 40" refId="ref9217" refString="THOMSON, C. G. 1858: Forsok till uppstallning af Sveriges Staphyliner. - Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps- Akademiens Forhandlinger 15: 27 - 40." type="journal article" year="1858">THOMSON, 1858</bibRefCitation>
, ma la ligula e la forma della spermateca sono molto differenti. La ligula del nuovo genere è intera e a forma di mezza luna a base ristretta, fig. 27, e non divisa in due rami a forma di Y come in 
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FCB0BFD123C3F90C" box="[891,989,1673,1696]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Acrotona</emphasis>
e 
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF964E07FC33BFD124BDF90D" authority="(Atheta)" box="[1016,1187,1673,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Atheta">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FC33BFD12421F90D" box="[1016,1087,1673,1697]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Atheta</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FB9ABFD12486F90D" box="[1105,1176,1673,1697]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Atheta</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
. La spermateca del nuovo genere, fig. 26, è composta di numerose spire ampie e strette. In 
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FC32BF912445F94C" box="[1017,1115,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Acrotona</emphasis>
le spire prossimali della spermateca sono da una a tre e ampie. Il nuovo genere si presenta come un intermedio tra 
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF964E07FB03BE512504F88D" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1837" box="[1224,1306,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Placusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FB03BE512504F88D" box="[1224,1306,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Placusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ERICH- SON, 1837, dei 
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF964E07FC08BE712437F8ED" authorityName="Mulsant &amp; Rey" authorityYear="1871" box="[963,1065,1833,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Placusini">Placusini</taxonomicName>
, che ha ligula intera, formula tarsale 4-4-5 e palpi labiali di 2 articoli, e 
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF964E07FB29BE112537F8CD" authorityName="THOMSON" authorityYear="1858" box="[1250,1321,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FB29BE112537F8CD" box="[1250,1321,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Atheta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
che ha formula tarsale 4-5-5 e palpi labiali di tre articoli, fig. 27. La forma della ligula del nuovo genere ricorda quello degli 
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF964E07FC9DBEF123AEF86D" box="[854,944,1961,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Athetini">Athetini</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF964E07FC7CBEF124CEF86D" authority="SAWADA, 1980" authorityName="SAWADA" authorityYear="1980" box="[951,1232,1961,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Codoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF964E07FC7CBEF12430F86D" box="[951,1070,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="94">Codoglossa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="774BE295FF964E07FBFEBEF124CEF86D" author="SAWADA, K." box="[1077,1232,1961,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="94" pagination="335 - 354" refId="ref9178" refString="SAWADA, K. 1980: Atheta and its allies of Southeast Asia (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). I. Reexamination of some species from Borneo and Singapore. - Pacific Insects 21: 335 - 354." type="journal article" year="1980">SAWADA, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
dell’Indonesia, ma nel nuovo genere essa è molto ristretta alla base e mancano due setole apicali. La spermateca del nuovo genere ha forma completamente differente da quella di 
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF954E04FF76B9B1212AFEAD" authorityName="SAWADA" authorityYear="1980" box="[189,308,233,257]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Codoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF954E04FF76B9B1212AFEAD" box="[189,308,233,257]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Codoglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
che è semplice ovvero non avvolta in spire. L’habitus del nuovo genere è simile a 
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF954E04FD86B85122B1FE8C" box="[589,687,265,288]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Acrotona</emphasis>
, quello di 
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF954E04FF76B871212AFEED" authorityName="SAWADA" authorityYear="1980" box="[189,308,297,321]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Codoglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF954E04FF76B871212AFEED" box="[189,308,297,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Codoglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a 
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF954E04FE85B87121A2FEED" box="[334,444,297,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Microdota</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="774BE295FF954E04FE08B87122A3FEED" author="MULSANT, M. E. &amp; REY, C." box="[451,701,297,321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" pagination="147 - 189" refId="ref8887" refString="MULSANT, M. E. &amp; REY, C. 1873: Description de divers Coleopteres Brevipennes nouveaux ou peu connus. - Opuscula Entomologica 15: 147 - 189." type="journal article" year="1873">MULSANT &amp; REY, 1873</bibRefCitation>
. Maxilla con palpo mascellare fig. 28, mento fig. 29.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="13659F64FF954E04FF76B8D122A1FE0D" blockId="2.[189,703,393,417]" box="[189,703,393,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF954E04FF76B8D12178FE0D" bold="true" box="[189,358,393,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Tipo del genere</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="D4DAE4E7FF954E04FEB8B8D12265FE0D" authority="Pace, 2014" authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="2014" box="[371,635,393,417]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xyronarchusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF954E04FEB8B8D12265FE0D" box="[371,635,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Xyronarchusa amazonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="3A9DFE0DFF954E04FD4CB8D222A1FE0D" box="[647,703,394,417]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="13659F64FF954E04FF76B891220AFDED" blockId="2.[189,794,457,578]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="21AE4376FF954E04FF76B8912128FE4D" bold="true" box="[189,310,457,481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="95">Etimologia</emphasis>
: Il nome del nuovo genere significa “Che è un rasoio antico” per la forma della ligula simile a un rasoio greco-romano antico, dal greco antico ξυρόν = rasoio, άρΧΑîος = antico e ούσΑ = che è.
</paragraph>
